public abstract class LipnExternalProgramGenericAnnotator
extends org.apache.uima.analysis_component.JCasAnnotator_ImplBase

This class is intended to be a super-class for all LIPN componants built using an encapsulated external program. It simply provides a few protected methods that these componants should always call in their own methods, as well as a few constants which they should refer to whenever needed. Important information for classes extending from this AE: there are a few parameters that you must include in the AE descriptor, namely TimeOut, CharacterCodingErrorReplacementValue and a path for the program location. The behaviour due to the CharacterCodingErrorReplacementValue parameter also requires to be cautious when reading the output from the external program: if a value is defined, then some chars in the input text transmitted to the process may have been replaced with this value. That's why when the output is read and possibly re-aligned with the original input there may be non matching chars: use appropriate options.

Method Detail

ensureLanguage

public java.lang.String ensureLanguage(java.lang.String maybeLanguage,
                                       org.apache.uima.jcas.JCas aJCas,
                                       java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> languageMap)
                                throws org.apache.uima.analysis_engine.AnalysisEngineProcessException
This method can be called at the beginning of the process method, in the case where the AE needs that the language is set. Depending on the fact that languageMap is null or not, it also checks that the language is valid for the component and converts it to the form that the external program expects (e.g. "fr" -> "FRENCH")

Parameters:
maybeLanguage - null or a string corresponding to a language (generally obtained as the language parameter of the AE)
aJCas - the CAS
languageMap - if not null, the method additionally checks that the language is valid (exists as a key) and returns its mapping.
Returns:
  • maybeLanguage (or languageMap.get(maybeLanguage)) if maybeLanguage is not null (higher priority),
  • the language defined in the CAS (or its mapping through languageMap) if it is defined and maybeLanguage is null (lower priority)
Throws:
org.apache.uima.analysis_engine.AnalysisEngineProcessException - if
  • maybeLanguage is null and there is no language defined in the CAS (no language error)
  • maybeLanguage is not null and does not contain the language as a key (invalid language error)

parseAnnotationFilter

public java.lang.String[][] parseAnnotationFilter(java.lang.String[] filter,
                                                  java.lang.String parameterName)
                                           throws org.apache.uima.resource.ResourceInitializationException
Creates two arrays of features names and values in order to build a constraint to filter annotations, based on a String[] parameter containing strings of the form 'featureName=featureValue'. The resulting constraint will be a 'AND' between all these conditions. See also createAnnotationFilterConstraint(JCas, int, String[][], boolean)

Parameters:
filter - the input string array
parameterName - the name of the parameter where this data was read, to provide an explicit error message.
Returns:
An array of size 2, containing two String arrays: the first one contains the names, the second one contains the values. This array can be used with createAnnotationFilterConstraint(JCas, int, String[][], boolean).
Throws:
org.apache.uima.resource.ResourceInitializationException - if the format is not satisfied

filterArrays - the result of parseAnnotationFilter: an array containing two String arrays (first for names, second for values)
threadSafe - whether CAS access should be synchronized or not
